<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>root about for something • root for something</xh5><p> <i>root about for something—</i>1. <i>(of pigs, etc.)</i> turn up the ground with the snout in search of food: A wild boar has been spotted <u>rooting about for</u> food scraps left behind by tourists. 2. search for smth. (by turning things over): He has been in the habit of taking more or less prolonged trips to the Continent for the purpose of <u>rooting about for</u> antiques.</p><p><i>root for something—</i>1. <i>(Sport)</i> support or encourage one’s favorite team: Most people tend to <u>root for</u> the team that dominates the local sports scene. 2. <i>= root about for something 1:</i> Digging in your purse or wallet like a hog <u>rooting for</u> acorns will always cast doubt in the mind of a bartender.</p> </entry>
